<br>
Jarasath Medallion<br>
-Top- Ancient Jarsath (Zone: Firiona Vie)<br>
I suggest passing by occasionally and asking random pally/sk/necro/clerics in the zone to sense undead for you, I tried camping him, killing everything around where he spawns but nothing worked.<br>
-Middle- Bloodgill Marauder (Zone: Lake of Ill Omen)<br>
easily soloable, just sneak in with an EB item on, and fight him in the little cave then sneak back out.<br>
-Bottom- Ground Spawn (Zone: Swamp of No Hope)<br>
no comment, too easy.<br>
<br>
Obulus Medallion<br>
-Top- Pained Soul (Zone: Trakanon's Teeth)<br>
Still havnt got this guy but I havnt been camping him much, one of his PH's is a ghost commander, thats lightblue to 60, he can hurt me alittle, so it makes you nervious the first time killing him but just get your bloodpoint out or something.<br>
-Middle- Rotting Skeleton (Zone: Dreadlands)<br>
This ones easy, just a static spawn.<br>
-Bottom- Burnished Wooden Staff (Zone: Warslilks Woods)<br>
This part, I went up and conned the iksar, he was KOS, so I illusioned iksar and conned again, he was indiffrent, so I swam over and handed the staff in and it worked just fine.<br>
<br>
Kylong Medallion<br>
-Top- Niblek (Zone: Chardok)<br>
I snuck solo down there about 2 days ago, real easy, just watch the dogs, con everything on the way down. I got to Niblek, got my piece and on my way back up something I had avoided earlier I had just ran past, I had a real good train going on my way up, but my AA mod run3 outran them really easily so I escaped that train wreck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
-Middle- Ground Spawn (Zone: Kaesora)<br>
this one, youve got to get a map of Kaesora for, the only thing that saw past my hidesneak were those stupid blood spider things, they have mean damageshields on them too, but that zone respawns really slow so you can solo pull them and kill them, have enough time to mend up and sneak the rest of the way down. Took me around 5 minutes to figure out how to get there, and how to get out again hehe.<br>
-Bottom- Verix Kyloxs remains (Zone: Karnor's Castle)<br>
have to get a group to camp this one, its just not soloable imo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
